# Build-context excludes for every image built from the repo root.
#
# qaroom-mcp moved from packages/ to services/ in Phase 3 (ADR-0006). In packages/ it was copied
# into every image by `COPY packages ./packages` and, depending on @qaroom/content + @qaroom/gateway
# (workspace:*) that a per-service image lacks, broke `pnpm install` (ERR_PNPM_WORKSPACE_PKG_NOT_FOUND)
# — hence the old exclude. Under services/ it is copied by no image (each Dockerfile copies only its
# own `services/<name>`), so no exclude is needed; the bloat and the install break are both gone.

# Never ship local installs, VCS, or build output into any image context.
**/node_modules
.git
**/dist
**/.venv
**/.turbo
